RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 1 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 77. Starter Allowance Purse 20000. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS SINCE JUNE 14, 2022. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since May 14 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since April 14 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CUENCA showed good early foot to set the early pace near the rail down the backstretch, edged clear around the far turn and had a long lead in the stretch under a steady hand ride. MONIQUES DAREDEVIL tracked the early leader two deep from the outside down the backstretch but was no match for the winner in the drive. DANCE A LITTLE JIG dropped back off the early going, raced six wide into the upper stretch, improved position over Serene Warrior in the stretch run and raced along for third place. SERENE WARRIOR prompt the early pace from the inside and tired. LADY FOX race far back to trailed throughout and was eased up on in the stretch run.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 2 5F Dirt CR: 81. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 19000. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $16,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $16,000 AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 14 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since April 14 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) Preference to horses with the most starts at Penn National since May 31st 2022. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at Five Furlongs.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OX DOC showed good early foot to the early pace and drew off to be well clear under steady handling. BOX OF JOE chased the pace from the outside, moved up five deep near the three sixteenths pole, came in near the eighth pole, forced Brit's Candyman to check sharply and finished willingly to the wire. Jockey of Brit's Candyman claimed objection against Box of Joe and stewards disqualified and placed Box of Joe fourth for interference in the stretch run. MIZZEN MAN chased the pace from the inside, continued a rail bid in the drive and moved up to improve position. BRIT'S CANDYMAN coaxed along early, checked sharply near the eighth pole, angled out and kept on the wire. SPOOKY ONE chased the early leader two deep from the outside and weakened the final eighth of a mile. SUNSHINE JACK was off slowly, raced off the early going and never was a factor. TAP EM stumbled at the break and trailed throughout.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 68. Claiming Purse 10800. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE DECEMBER 14. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 14 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROSES FROM HEAVEN showed good early speed from the outside racing two deep and edge clear late under strong handling. STARSHIP REINA was bumped soundly at the start, pressed the early lead from the inside and kept on gamely to the wire. PRINCESS KAIRA was shuffled back at the break, moved up three deep near the quarter pole to challenge and finished willingly to the wire. FIVE DAYS IN MAY bumped soundly at the break, inside nearing the three eighths pole, angled out through the far turn, raced from the far outside in the stretch and gained ground late. JACK'S LILLY settled off the early going, raced four wide into the upper stretch and lacked a rally. HAY BUCK stalked the top pair early on and weakened while racing two to three wide.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HERE'S WALDO sent clear from the outside and held gamely in the drive to be well clear under strong encouragement. FACTOTUM tracked the early leader from the outside two deep, raced three to four wide in the stretch drive and finished willingly to the wire. DEVOTED KITTEN settled off the early pace, raced along the inside past the quarter pole, took aim into the upper stretch, shifted out three wide and flattened out. RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOLDEN TREASURE settled off the early pace along the inside, continued its run from the inside into the upper stretch, angled three wide between rivals near the eighth pole and finished strongly to prove best under steady handling. I DON'T SEE COLORS was bumped, in tight at the break, moved up along the inside near the quarter pole, angled to race four wide and finished well to get up for the place position. WARRIOR'S PAYOFF pressed the early pace from the inside, had a narrow lead near the eighth pole and weakened in the final stages. IF WE GET LUCKY vied two deep and was empty inside the eighth pole. BOB'S OUR UNCLE stalked the pace and had no rally while racing from the outside. NORTHERN VIRGINIA was bumped soundly at the start, raced two to three deep in the drive and never was a factor. BARN SWALLOW was bumped at the break, race mid pack early on, raced six wide into the upper stretch and never threatened. UPTOWNJACOB BROWN dropped back off the early pace, raced four to five wide around the far turn and never was a factor. SYLVIA I AM was void of early speed, raced from the outside in the stretch and never menaced. ONE TRUTH vied for the early lead from the inside and tired readily. PER RULING FROM THE PENNSYLVANIA RACING COMMISSION, I DON'T SEE COLORS WAS DISQUALIFIED DUE TO INELIGIBILITY.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DON'T QUESTION ME rated along under a hold two deep, moved through the far turn, raced from the outside of rivals in the stretch and surged clear racing four to five wide under steady pressure. OVER THE BORDER settled to race mid pack early on, moved up three wide near the quarter pole to challenge for the lead and kept on gamely to the wire. MISCHIEF WARRIOR tracked the early leader racing two deep, raced two wide between rivals in the drive and kept on willingly to the wire. WHISKIED UP sprinted clear early on, met mid just past the three eighths pole and weakened a bit in the final stages. MARY'S LITTLE MAN was off slowly, raced near the inside and never threatened.
